info.name: WHOIS XML APIs
info.description:
This is a Postman Collection for the WhoisXMLAPI endpoints.

Refer to the [WhoisXMLAPI website](https://whoisxmlapi.com) for more details.

If you have an API-related question, you can ask them here: [https://main.whoisxmlapi.com/contact-us](https://main.whoisxmlapi.com/contact-us)

## Installation

### Manual install

You can download this Collection from a GitHub repo here: [https://github.com/whois-api-llc/postman-whoisxmlapi](https://github.com/whois-api-llc/postman-whoisxmlapi)

## Environment

This Collection includes a pre-configured Environment. You will need to set up the following variables in order to run each request:

| Name | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `api_key` | Your API key |

item.description:
Brand Alert API searches across all recently registered & deleted domain names and returns result sets consisting of domain names containing terms you specify.

Full API documentation is availableÂ [here](https://brand-alert.whoisxmlapi.com/api/documentation/making-requests).

item.description:
Bulk WHOIS API gives you parsed domain WHOIS ownership information for a list of domains and IP addresses.

Full API documentation is availableÂ [here](https://whois.whoisxmlapi.com/bulk-api/documentation/making-requests).

item.name: DNS Lookup API

query.description: The target domain name.
DNS type: A, NS, SOA, MX, etc. You can specify multiple comma-separated values, e.g., A,SOA,TXT; all records can be retrieved with type=_all.
Response output format. Acceptable values: JSON | XML.
A javascript function used when outputFormat is JSON.

'full' - all the data and the tests will be processed.

fast - waiting for the document.load event. slow - waiting for network idle event.

If specified (any value), disables JS.
Custom delay (ms) before screen capture.
Custom timeout (ms) for page loading. API will respond with an error if our server can't load the page within the specified timeout.
deviceScaleFactor value for the emulator.

response.name: Get the domain availability status

query.description: The domain/IPv4/IPv6/email address for which WHOIS data is requested.
Response output format.
1 results in getting the latest WHOIS record even if it's incomplete.
1 results in a quick check on domain availability, 2 is slower but more accurate.
1 results in returning IPs for the domain name.
1 results in returning the WHOIS record for the hosting IP if the WHOIS record for the tld of the input domain is not supported.
1 results in fetching proxy/WHOIS guard data, if it exists.
1 results in returning WHOIS data from registry only, without fetching data from registrar.
1 results in stripping all raw text from the output.
A javascript function used when outputFormat is JSON.
1 provides parsing for input WHOIS raw texts.
A string representing the registry WHOIS raw text to be parsed.
A string representing the registrar WHOIS raw text to be parsed.
1 results in getting fresh data

WHOIS API service provides the registration details, also known as the WHOIS record data, of a domain name, an IP address, or an email address.

Full API documentation is available [here](https://whois.whoisxmlapi.com/documentation/making-requests).
